<h2>Server Features</h2>
<hr />

<font size="3" color="#cc0000">
<BlockQuote>
This list is NOT comprehensive but serves only as a highlight.
</BlockQuote>
</font>

<ul>
    <li><b>Configuration and Compliance</b>
        <ul>
            <li>Fully configurable through XML and Management Interface.</li>
            <li>Site setting are inherited from base settings (Global and Local settings).</li>
            <li>Configuration area segmentation.</li>
            <li>Highly configurable Content Compression and Caching</li>
            <li>Default Pages.</li>
            <li>Virtual Roots.</li>
            <li>Mime Types.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<ul>
    <li><b>Protection</b>
        <ul>
            <li>IP Filters (Low level rejection).</li>
            <li>URL Filters (Can include URI and request string).</li>
            <li>Extension Filters</li>
            <li>Custom Filter / Plugin support.</li>
            <li>Built on top of secure C++ stdlib.</li>
            <li>AD and Local user impersonation.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<ul>
    <li><b>HTTP 1.0 / 1.1</b>
        <ul>
            <li>Supports GET, POST, HEAD and PUT methods.</li>
            <li>Content Ranges.</li>
            <li>Download Resume.</li>
            <li>Keep-Alive.</li>
            <li>Multipart form-data / post data.</li>
            <li>Header reader chunking.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<ul>
    <li><b>Scripting:</b>
        <ul>
            <li>CGI (Common Gateway Interface)</li>
            <li>CGI / bin folders support.</li>
            <li>Full SSI (Server Side Include) implementation</li>
            <li>External Scripting engines (e.g. PHP, PERL, Python, etc.)</li>
            <li>Native executables (e.g. exe & com files)</li>
            <li>Native scripts (e.g. bat & cmd files)</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<ul>
    <li><b>Built in Performance:</b>
        <ul>
            <li>Supports compression (GZip / Deflate).</li>
            <li>Compresses static content with caching.</li>
            <li>Supports dynamic content compression.</li>
            <li>Caching engine maintains most hit / least used items to push items from cache.</li>
            <li>Dynamic connection thread pooling delivers performance & resource efficiency.</li>
            <li>One instance supports 1,000 simultaneous connections per site.
                <ul>
                    <li>Benchmarked at over 80MB/s per connection until thread count reaches thread/CPU critical mass.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>
